Current OSCAR/ICQ endpoint notes
--------------------------------

Hardcoded endpoint inventory in this tree:

  libpurple/protocols/oscar/faimconfig.h
    FAIM_LOGIN_SERVER = icq.petaltxt.me
    FAIM_LOGIN_PORT = 5190

  libpurple/protocols/oscar/oscar.c
    Auth bootstrap fallback reads account options:
      server (default from FAIM_LOGIN_SERVER)
      port (default from FAIM_LOGIN_PORT)
    Redirected services use server-provided host:port pairs from BOS/auth redirects.
    DirectIM and OFT listen ranges are fixed at 5190-5199.
    Legacy hash lookup defaults (disabled by default):
      legacy_hash_lookup_host = gaim.sourceforge.net
      legacy_hash_lookup_port = 80
      legacy_hash_lookup_path = /aim_data.php3

Known-supported targets
-----------------------

Verified against https://petaltxt.me/connect.php:

  Primary ICQ/OSCAR endpoint:
    host: icq.petaltxt.me
    port: 5190/TCP

  Legacy AIM endpoint (older AIM clients <= 5.1):
    host: login.petaltxt.me
    port: 5190/TCP

For this plugin, operators can override Auth host/port in account settings without recompiling.
The login bootstrap path uses Auth host/port for the initial authorizer connection, then follows
server-provided BOS and service redirects.

Limitations
-----------

The old web hash fetch flow for AIM memrequest data uses a historic sourceforge endpoint and may
not be available on modern deployments. It is now gated by account option
"allow_legacy_hash_lookup" and disabled by default so login/session startup does not depend on
that external URL.
